reviewBlob:
Bomber from total Wine Tucson. This is a fantastic big brew! Nice pour with a huge o head. High in hoppy flavor. Lots of citrus. Very refreshing. 
Enjoy!
Bomber from Dchmela. A full bodied beer bursting with clove roasty malt and barley. I bet this pairs well with a nice steak!

beerName: Widmer Brothers Rotator IPA Series - Shaddock IPA
reviewBlob:
12 oz Bottle at Memphis Meis in Ossining NY. 
Nice deep golden pour with a fluffy head. Hops, Grapfruit and pine with just a hint of Cinnimon keep this beer highly refreshing while eating NY BBQ. 
Enjoy!

beerName: Laughing Dog Sneaky Pete Imperial IPA
reviewBlob: Bomber from Tucson Total wine. Dark amber pour with a nice head. A little to heavy on the resin side. Unbalenced on the malt and alcohol. On the bottom of the list for Laughing Dog.
750ml bottle care of Dchmela! Thanks Dave! Nice cloudy brown pour with a hugeo head! Spicy deliciousness all around. Chocholet coffee rosted barley and malts. Rasins rind round off the finish. Yum!
Bomber from Fred. Thanks Fred. This is a good beer. Very seasonal. Spicy and good. Its a nice match for the impieral Stout. Go find yourself some!

beerName: Southern Star Pine Belt Pale Ale
reviewBlob: 16oz Can thanks to Fred! Boy! This beer sure is Pinie!. Nice and dry with a hopy middle and a nice Rye after taste. A very refreshing brew.

Bomber bottle care of Dchmela. Thanks man!
This beer rocked! Nice cloudy golden pour with a nice head. Full mouth of flavor. Ginger Cinnimon hops with lots o spice!
Go find some!

beerName: Captain Lawrence Birra DeCicco - Limone Luppolo
reviewBlob:
Bomber bottle right from the brewery in Elmsford NY. 
Nice cloudy golden pour with a thin head an very nice lacing. Thick delicious fruity twang with lime and ginger. A very refreashing brew! Thanx Scott!
Holy Cow this is a Big Beer! Thanks Dchmela! Nice dark pour with a light brown thick foamy head. Roasted barly and pine. Booming thick rich flavor with a bit of chocholet. Great pallat!

beerName: Cigar City Batch #69 Double Cream Ale
reviewBlob: Bomber from DChmela. U Rock! Nice cloudy golden pour with very little head, (You know how much I like head!) Very smooth and delicious. Grapefruit and nuts, big middle and excellent palette. Glad I cracked it open!

beerName: Terrapin Side Project Captn Krunkles Black IPA
reviewBlob: Bomber bottle from Dchmela, ( thanks Dave ). Nice black pour with a fine tan head. Roasted barly goodness with a nice balance of hops with a little wheat. Every sip was a pleasure.

Bomber bottle care of Dchmela. (you da man!). Dark copper pour with a thick head. Delicious spices balanced very well with hops and alcohol. 
A nice seasonal that should be repeated!

12 oz bottle. This is an interesting beer. Full of spicy flavors. Nice balance of yeast barley liqurish and pine nuts. 
Great Glutin free brew!
12oz bottle from Beverage World. Peekskill, NY. A match made in heaven. Deep brown pour with a this whispy head. Great flavor all around. A fine balance of spicy goodness. yeaaaaa!
Bottle. Little Bs. Tarrytown NY. Nice dark brown pour with a thin head. Roasty goodness wrapped around Chocolet rasins coffee cream and spice. Excelent Palett!
Pint Can. This was sure a nice wake me up for my palat. Full flavors like pineapple and grapefruit. Nice fluffy head. Excellent palat.

beerName: Blue Point No Apologies Imperial IPA
reviewBlob: Bomber. Nice golden cloudy pour with a small head. Lots of flavor. Grapefruit pineapples and pine. Nice balance of bitter and hops. Go for it.
12oz Skim Can. Wow! This is one tasty beer! Full of nice fruity flavors like Grapfruit and oranges. Big hop slap in the face with a golden bitter finish. Fantastic!
On Tap at the brewery. Nice golden pour with a nice head. This beer is packed with great flavor. Hops, spices, mint, rounded off with a touch of cinnamon. Nice pallet. Congrats guys!

Bomber bottle that came in a great Super trade with Daknole. (thanks man!) this is an unique beer. Dark pour with a nice head. Bold flavorful frOnt end full of tequila roasted malts and zest. Fantastic with Mexican or BBQ. 
Enjoy!
Growler from my Pal Fred. Nice dark Charamel pour with a thick head. Rosted Barley Charamel hops with a great pallet. This beer needs to be more accessible.

beerName: Flying Dog In de Wildeman Farmhouse IPA
reviewBlob:
On Tap. Little Bs Tarrytown NY. Hazy light golden pour with a big head! 
Im not to big on the Siason yeast to begin with but at first taste this is a very good refreshing beer. Its the back end that fall off the cliff with me. A lite to floral and tart. Then again if your into that kinda thing this beer is for you!
On Tap. Bridge View Tavern. Now thats a good beer. Deep charamel pour with a thin head. Rich roasted barley taste. Sweet hoppy goodness. Go for it.

beerName: Lagunitas Were Only In It For The Money
reviewBlob: Bomber from Decicco Ardsley NY. Nice golden pour with a thick head. Dry grassy (in a good way) hoppy with no hints if anything! Nice homage to Frank!

brewerName: Port Brewing Co / The Lost Abbey
reviewBlob: 12.7 oz bottle thanks to Daknole! Pour is nice and thick with A thin whisp of head. Chocholet raisin coffee and butterscotch. Deep spicy favor that last and last. Fantastic!
UPDATED: SEP 5, 2012

12.7 fl. Oz bottle from my AZ ratebeer crew!
I had no intention to get loaded last night but thats what happens when you dont share a bottle of big and worse. Fewwww! 
This was to boozy to taste the hints of Chocolet, pine and roasted barley. 
It just didnt matter.  Im still tasting it today.

Bomber from Total wine Tucson. I picked up this beer for I wanted to taste what was happening in AZ. Ok. Light golden pour with a thin head. It is almost sourer y  and I hate sours but I wont hold that against it. But I did not like this beer at all. to much carbonation and a grassy battery acid taste. good thing it is my 301 rating. I would have hated that cool 300 cartoon to have come up on this beer.

beerName: Hoppin Frog Hop Masters Abbey Belgian-Style Double IPA
reviewBlob: Bomber from a trade with Dchmela! Nice golden pour with a think head! lots of flavor including nuts pine hops, lots of hops with a good balance of alcohol. Been waiting to try this beer for a long time. Thanks Dchmela!

Bomber from Total Wine in Tucson AZ. Deep golden pour with a think head.Very dry with raisins, malt, dry hops and bit of spice. Heavy on the alcohol though. No wonder its called Old Thumper. Glad I tasted it now its time to move on.

Bomber bottle from a trade with Dchmela. NIce deep golden pour with a big head! Very flavorful with grapefruit hops spices and barley all with incredible balance. This one was worth waiting for!
thanks Dchmela!
Bomber from Total Wines Tucson. Beautiful golden pour with a nice head. Big front end but balanced just right with hopy goodness. Wish I had more.
Bomber Bottle from Total Wine Tucson. A very Big beer. Golden think pour with a fluffy head. Nice balance of favors. Lots of great hops and citrus. Very nice.

Bomber Bottle from Total Wine Tucson. Nice cloudy pour with a thin head. Nutty yeasty with a hint of rasin and grapefruit. 
Nice balance of all.

On tap. Bridge view Tavern. Well if your gonna drink this dont drink any other beer before. Nice red golden pour with a thick head. O very hoppy. In fact its all hops. Its so overpowering that I fails to taste anything else. So go ahead and try this. But make it your first beer.

On Tap. Bridge View Tavern Sleepy Hollow NY. 
Fantastic black pour with a thin head. Lots of flavor. Hops barly and malt (of course) with a nice balance throughout. 
Go for it.

Bomber Bottle from Total Wine Tucson Az! This is one fine brew! Nice golden pour with some nice head there! So robust, so fruity and O SO HOPPY! well balanced and yummy! Epic does it once again! Find this!

Bomber bottle. Nice dark pour with a thin head. Smooth delicious flavor. Sweet bitter cherry with some chocholet. 
Enjoy

750 mil bottle from Fastpass! Big thick pour with a light brown head. Heavy bourbon front end that transforms to cherry chocholet spice. 
A very nice beer!
12 oz bottle. Fresh clean bug Ale taste right away. Good pour with a this head. Big bite in the end. Nice and bitter.

Bomber bottle from fastpass. Thanks man. 
A big mouth of boozey spicy flavore. Thin head and a cloudy look.

beerName: Oskar Blues Deviant Dales India Pale Ale
reviewBlob: On Tap Noble Hops Tucson AZ. Nice pour with a big foamy head. Great for an IPA. Very hoppy very citrusy. Nice bite but unbalanced with the alcohol. That didnt stop me from ordering two!

beerName: Big Sky Moose Drool Brown Ale
reviewBlob:
On Tap. At The Hub. Downtown Tucson AZ. Just before seeing the Dweezle Zappa Show! O what a find this was! Moose Drool on tap! Thick brown pour with a nice head. Brown nutty goodness with a nice zesty spice from within. Roasted dark malt with smokey barly on the palet!
Yumm
12 oZ bottle from my AriZona crew buds. This beer was a kick in the head! Dark brown pour with a nice tan head. Heavy coffee and chocolate. Rosty malt deep zesty goodness. Kept me up for hours.

Bomber bottle from Dchmela. # 990 of 1000. A thick black pour with a thin head. Very lacie and unbalanced between roasty malts and the alcohol. But after a few sips evened out well. Rich and dark. Just the way I like it!
12 oz bottle from Dchmela. Big fat beer here! A facefull of flavor. Zesty spice, clove. Very good balance of everything.

Bomber from total Wine Tucson. Nice pour with a fluffy head.  Bold hopy start. Bold fruity with a big bottom. Nice long lasting pallet. 
Enjoy

Bomber from total wine Tucson AZ. Deep golden pour with a nice foamy head. Big hopy start followed by caramel grapefruit and other citrus flavors. Nice carbonation and very well balanced. 
Cheers!

brewerName: Port Brewing Co / The Lost Abbey
reviewBlob: On tap. Noble Hops Tucson AZ! Nice golden cloudy pour with a Thin head. Nice fruity hoppy taste. Grapfruit, orange, just like a good double IPA. This is a delicious beer!
